{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"842f5520-8754-47ca-98a5-2b0860c98463","content":"The issue is **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_auBQagk4D9dzigGDmETmB2","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-a7853f9e833a4d358622524d98732b35/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-a7853f9e833a4d358622524d98732b35/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"4efe318b-dbde-4664-a783-ca3b45d3ba54","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, so it can't see the `Domain` module. The fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first.","outputTokens":384,"requestId":"0415:2AE020:429835:4DEDAB:69F00428"},"id":"31b5910a-c456-4da1-b638-5fa935341f50","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:49:51.641Z","parentId":"d44a9abb-2cd4-4a26-94bb-7d2a89382918"}
